Testing
-------
  
  cd npg_qc_viewer
  unset CATALYST_HOME #if set
  perl Build.PL --installjsdeps
  ./Build
  TEST_AUTHOR=1 ./Build test

Using npm:
  npm test

Using grunt:
  grunt -v
  
  or for testing by file name pattern match:

  grunt test:<pattern>.html (e.g. `grunt test:*qc*.html`)

In browser javascript testing - open files in a browser window:
  t/client/test.html
  t/client/test_format_for_csv.html
  t/client/test_modify_on_view.html
  t/client/test_qc_outcomes_view.html
  t/client/test_qc_page.html
  t/client/test_qc_utils.html
  t/client/test_collapser.html

Running your own development server
-----------------------------------

  bin/npg_qc_viewer_server.pl -p YOUR_PORT

To test manual qc functionality, edit the decryption_key value in npg_qc_viewer.conf

To enable debugging set CATALYST_DEBUG=1

Using custom bcviz
------------------

In bcviz (your working copy) run 'bower link'.
In npg-qc, npg_qc_viewer directory, run 'bower link bcviz'.

Testing with webdriver:

  Server 
    # Starting inside project folder (npg_qc)
    pushd npg_qc_viewer 
    # Create a .npg folder and populate with test configuration files
    # If bower dependencies haven't been installed:
    bower install
    export PERL5LIB=t/client/lib:lib:$PERL5LIB

    Run server
      HOME=./ dev=dev CATALYST_CONFIG=t/client/npg_qc_viewer_integration.conf bin/npg_qc_viewer_server.pl -p 38000

  Testing with webdriverjs:
  
    Run webdriver script to start a client
      # If needed, ssh to client with X11 forwarding enabled (ssh -Y servername)
      # Starting inside project folder (npg_qc)
      pushd npg_qc_viewer
      npm install --only=dev
      HTTP_PORT=38000 node t/client/integration/changeLanePreliminaryOutcome.js
      popd

  Testing with Selenium::Remote::Driver

    Run client script
      # If needed, ssh to client with X11 forwarding enabled (ssh -Y servername)
      # Starting inside project folder (npg_qc)
      pushd npg_qc_viewer
      HTTP_PORT=38000 perl t/client/integration/changeLanePreliminaryOutcome.pl
      popd
